    <item>
      <title>Yuan112 - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan112/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan112/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.18&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify an XML External Entity (XXE) vulnerability to recover user credentials, gain initial access through SSH, and escalate privileges by abusing an insecure URL validation script executed with sudo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/yuan112/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine Information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.18 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1 Debian 5+deb11u3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.62 (Debian)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and an Apache web server were exposed, so I began with web enumeration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
